description: Prevent silent fallback/workaround patterns; require justified, documented fallbacks
alwaysApply: true
---

# Avoid fallback workarounds and silent extraction

Purpose
- Do not rely on brittle client/server fallbacks or implicit "workarounds" (for example: parsing JSON out of system messages, auto-extracting data from prompts, or silently switching models) as normal control flow.

Policy
- Never use automatic fallbacks that hide failures from developers or users. A fallback is allowed only when there is a documented reason, a test demonstrating safety, and an accompanying log & persisted diagnostic field.
- Do not extract structured data from system-role messages as an implicit persistence mechanism. Server and client must exchange structured data explicitly via well-defined fields (e.g., `gameSetup.generatedCharacter`) in API payloads.
- Do not silently switch models, APIs, or endpoints without:
  1) an explicit justification in code (comment + link to issue/PR), and
  2) observable telemetry persisted to the GameState (e.g., `llmCallError`, `llmCallStartedAt`, `llmCallCompletedAt`).

How to apply
- Apply to backend code that interacts with LLMs or persists game state (examples: `go/internal/llm/`, `go/internal/gamesession/`, `go/internal/httpserver/`, `go/internal/persist/`).
- When adding a fallback, require:
  - A short rationale in code comments and the PR description.
  - Persisted diagnostic fields (error message, timestamps) to GameState.
  - No user-visible masking of the failure; surface errors to the client with actionable messages.

Bad example
```js
// ❌ BAD: silently parse player data from a system message when save fails
const jsonMatch = systemMessageContent.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
if (jsonMatch) {
  gameSetup.generatedCharacter = JSON.parse(jsonMatch[0]); // brittle
}
```

Good example
```js
// ✅ GOOD: require explicit field and persist on successful generation
if (parsed && parsed.playerCharacter) {
  await GameState.findOneAndUpdate({ gameId }, { $set: { 'gameSetup.generatedCharacter': parsed.playerCharacter } });
} else {
  // surface error to client and persist rawModelOutput for debugging
}
```

Enforcement
- This rule is always active. When modifying LLM interaction code, add log lines and persist diagnostics rather than adding silent fallbacks.

